obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3084)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3084&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Public Records Act, 1993.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.1st March, 1995, vide notification No. S.O. 128(E), dated 1st March, 1995, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii)`
  line
  line `This Act has been extended to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3085)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3085&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Archival Advisory Board constituted under sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(b) "Director General" means the Director General of Archives appointed by the Central`
  line `Government and includes any officer authorised by that Government to perform the duties of the`
  line `Director General;`
  line
  line `(c) "head of the Archives" means a person holding the charge of the Archives of the Union`
  line `territory Administration;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "public records" includes`
  line
  line `(i) any document, manuscript and file;`
  line
  line `(ii) any microfilm, microfiche and facsimile copy of a document;`
  line
  line `(iii) any reproduction of image or images embodied in such microfilm (whether enlarged or`
  line `not); and`
  line
  line `(iv) any other material produced by a computer or by any other device,`
  line `of any records creating agency;`
  line
  line `(f) records creating agency includes,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to the Central Government, any ministry, department or office of that`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any statutory body or corporation wholly or substantially controlled or`
  line `financed by the Central Government or commission or any committee constituted by that`
  line `Government, the offices of the said body, corporation, commission or committee;`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to a Union territory Administration, any department or office of that`
  line Administration;
  line
  line `(iv) in relation to any statutory body or corporation wholly or substantially controlled or`
  line `financed by Union territory Administration or commission or any committee constituted by that`
  line `Administration, the offices of the said body, corporation, commission or committee;`
  line
  line `(g) "records officer" means the officer nominated by the records creating agency under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3086)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of the Central Government to coordinate, regulate and supervise operations connected with administration, management, etc., of public records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3086&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall have`
  line `the power to coordinate, regulate and supervise the operations connected with the administration,`
  line `management, preservation, selection, disposal and retirement of public records under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government in relation to the public records of the records creating agencies`
  line `specified in sub-clauses (i) and (ii) of clause (f) of section 2 and the Union territory Administration in`
  line `relation to the public records of the records creating agencies specified in sub-clauses (iii) and (iv) of the`
  line `said clause, may, by order, authorise the Director General or the head of the Archives, as the case may be,`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified in the order, to carry out all or any of the following`
  line `functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) supervision, management and control of the Archives.`
  line
  line `(b) acceptance for deposit of public records of permanent nature after such period as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(c) custody, use and withdrawal of public records;`
  line
  line `(d) arrangement, preservation and exhibition of public records;`
  line
  line `(e) preparation of inventories, indices, catalogues and other reference media of public records;`
  line
  line `(f) analysing, developing, promoting and coordinating the standards, procedures and the`
  line `techniques for improvement of the records management system;`
  line
  line `(g) ensuring the maintenance, arrangement and security of public records in the Archives and in`
  line `the offices of the records creating agency;`
  line
  line `(h) promoting utilisation of available space and maintenance of equipments for preserving public`
  line records;
  line
  line `(i) tendering advice to records creating agencies on the compilation, classification and disposal of`
  line `records and application of standards, procedures and techniques of records management;`
  line
  line `(j) survey and inspection of public records;`
  line
  line `(k) organising training programmes in various disciplines of Archives administration and records`
  line management;
  line
  line `(l) accepting records from any private source;`
  line
  line `(m) regulating access to public records;`
  line
  line `(n) receiving records from defunct bodies and making arrangement for securing public records in`
  line `the event of national emergency;`
  line
  line `(o) receiving reports on records management and disposal practices from the records officer;`
  line
  line `(p) providing authenticated copies of, or extracts from, public records;`
  line
  line `(q) destroying or disposal of public records;`
  line
  line `(r) obtaining on lease or purchasing or accepting as gift any document of historical or national`
  line importance.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3087)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Prohibition against taking of public records out of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3087&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `No person shall take or cause to be`
  line `taken out of India any public records without the prior approval of the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such prior approval shall be required if any public records are taken or sent out of`
  line `India for any official purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3088)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Records officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3088&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every records creating agency shall nominate one of its officers as records`
  line `officer to discharge the functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every records creating agency may set up such number of record rooms in such places as it deems`
  line `fit and shall place each record room under the charge of a records officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3089)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Responsibilities of records officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3089&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The records officer shall be responsible for--`
  line
  line `(a) proper arrangement, maintenance and preservation of public records under his charge;`
  line
  line `(b) periodical review of all public records and weeding out public records of euphemeral value;`
  line
  line `(c) appraisal of public records which are more than twenty-five years old in consultation with the`
  line `National Archives of India or, as the case may be, the Archives of the Union territory with a view to`
  line `retaining public records of permanent value;`
  line
  line `(d) destruction of public records in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(e) compilation of a schedule of retention for public records in consultation with the National`
  line `Archives of India or, as the case may be, the Archives of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(f) periodical review for downgrading of classified public records in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(g) adoption of such standards, procedures and techniques as may be recommended from time to`
  line `time by the National Archives of India for improvement of record management system and`
  line `maintenance of security of public records;`
  line
  line `(h) compilation of annual indices of public records;`
  line
  line `(i) compilation of organisational history and annual supplement thereto;`
  line
  line `(j) assisting the National Archives of India or, as the case may be, the Archives of the Union`
  line `territory for public records management;`
  line
  line `(k) submission of annual report to the Director General or, as the case may be, head of the`
  line `Archives in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(l) transferring of records of any defunct body to the National Archives of India or the Archives`
  line `of the Union territory, as the case may be, for preservation.`
  line
  line `(2) The records officer shall act under the direction of the Director General or, as the case may be,`
  line `head of the Archives while discharging the responsibilities specified in sub-section (1)`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3090)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Records officer to take appropriate action in the event of unauthorised removal, destruction, etc., of public records in his custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3090&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The records officer shall, in the event of any unauthorised`
  line `removal destruction, defacement or alteration of any public records under his charge, forthwith take`
  line `appropriate action for the recovery or restoration of such public records.`
  line
  line `(2) The records officer shall submit a report in writing to the Director General or, as the case may be,`
  line `the head of the Archives without any delay on any information about any unauthorised removal,`
  line `destruction, defacement or alteration of any public records under his charge and about the action initiated`
  line `by him and shall take action as he may deem necessary subject to the directions, if any, given by the`
  line `Director General or, as the case may be, head of the Archives.`
  line
  line `(3) The records officer may seek assistance from any government officer or any other person for the`
  line `purpose of recovery or restoration of public records and such officer or person shall render all assistance`
  line `to the records officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3091)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Destruction or disposal of public records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3091&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in any law for the`
  line `time being in force, no public record shall be destroyed or otherwise disposed of except in such manner`
  line `and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No record created before the year 1892 shall be destroyed except where in the opinion of the`
  line `Director General or, as the case may be, the head of the Archives, it is so defaced or is in such condition`
  line `that it cannot be put to any archival use.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3092)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Penalty for contraventions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3092&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any of the provisions of section 4 or section 8`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3093)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Public records bearing security classification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3093&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No public records bearing security`
  line `classification shall be transferred to the National Archives of India or the Archives of the Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3094)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Receipt of records from private sources.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3094&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Archives of India or the Archives`
  line `of the Union territory may accept any record of historical or national importance from any private source`
  line `by way of gift, purchase or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Archives of India or, as the case may be, the Archives of any Union territory may, in`
  line `such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, make any record referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) available to any bona fide research scholar.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3095)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Access to public records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3095&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) All unclassified public records as are more than thirty years old`
  line `and are transferred to the National Archives of India or the Archives of the Union territory may be,`
  line `subject to such exceptions and restrictions as may be prescribed made available to any bona fide research`
  line scholar.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the period of thirty years shall be reckoned from`
  line `the year of the opening of the public record.`
  line
  line `(2) Any records creating agency may grant to any person access to any public record in its custody in`
  line `such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3096)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Archival Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3096&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, constitute an Archival Advisory Board for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry of`
  line `Central Government dealing with Culture`
  line
  line `Chairman, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) one officer not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India, each from the Cabinet`
  line `Secretariat, Ministry of Home Affairs,Ministry of`
  line `Defence, Ministry of External Affairs, Ministry of`
  line `Finance and Ministry of Personnel, Public Grievances`
  line `and Pension`
  line
  line `Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) two representatives not below the rank of Joint`
  line `Secretary in the Union territory Administrations to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government`
  line
  line Members;
  line
  line `(d) three persons to be nominated by the Central`
  line `Government for a period not exceeding three years,`
  line `one being an Archivist and two being Professors in the`
  line `Post-graduate Department of History in any recognised`
  line University.
  line
  line Members;
  line
  line `(e) Director General`
  line
  line `Member-Secretary, ex officio`
  line
  line `(3) The members nominated under clause (d) of sub-section (2) shall be paid such allowances as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3097)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3097&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) advise the Central Government and Union territory Administrations on matters concerning the`
  line `administration, management, conservation and use of public records;`
  line
  line `(b) lay down guidelines for training of Archivists;`
  line
  line `(c) give directions for acquisition of records from private custody;`
  line
  line `(d) deal with such other matters as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (3098)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of the Director General to lay down norms and standards for courses in archival science.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3098&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Director General shall have the power to lay down norms and standards for courses`
  line `curricula, assessment and examinations relating to the training in archival science and other ancillary`
  line subjects.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (3099)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3099&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against any person in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (3100)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3100&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the period after which public records of permanent nature may be accepted under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which public records can be destroyed`
  line `under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which periodical review of classified public records for downgrading shall be`
  line `undertaken under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which the records officer will report to the Director General or the head of the`
  line `Archives under clause (k) of sub section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which public records may be destroyed or`
  line `disposed of under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which records of historical or national`
  line `importance may be made available to research scholar under sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) exceptions and restrictions subject to which public records may be made available to a`
  line `research scholar under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which any records creating agency may`
  line `grant to any person access to public records in its custody under sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(i) the allowances payable to members of the Board under sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(j) the matters with respect to which the Board may perform its functions under clause (d) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (3101)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Laying of rules before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041&sectionId=3101&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00007_199369_1517807323041
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the`
  line `rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
